---

<section id="about" class="py-24 px-6 section-alt">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr] gap-12 items-start">
      <!-- Left: Title + decorative -->
      <div>
        <span class="font-fira text-xs text-accent tracking-widest uppercase block mb-3">Who I Am</span>
        <h2 class="font-sora text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold section-title">About Me</h2>
        <div class="mt-12 hidden md:block">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-card border border-border">
              <div class="font-sora text-2xl font-bold text-accent">10+</div>
              <div class="font-fira text-xs text-muted mt-1">Years Building</div>
            </div>
            <div class="p-4 rounded-lg bg-card border border-border">
              <div class="font-sora text-2xl font-bold text-accent">30+</div>
              <div class="font-fira text-xs text-muted mt-1">Clients Shipped</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: Content -->
      <div>
        <div class="space-y-5 text-muted leading-relaxed text-base md:text-lg">
          <p>
            I started writing code in 2015. Within three years, I was deep in <span class="text-text font-medium">Solidity</span>,
            building smart contracts that would go on to help projects raise <span class="text-text font-medium">over $5 million</span>.
            That hands-on experience — deploying contracts that handle real funds, real users, real stakes —
            shaped everything about how I approach blockchain engineering today.
          </p>
          <p>
            Through <span class="text-text font-medium">Code Minto</span>, the company I founded, I've worked with
            <span class="text-text font-medium">30+ clients</span> to architect and ship production blockchain systems —
            DeFi protocols, tokenization platforms, staking contracts, NFT marketplaces, and multi-chain integrations.
            I was part of the core team at <span class="text-text font-medium">Velvet Capital</span> building DeFi asset management infrastructure,
            and at <span class="text-text font-medium">Private AI</span> I built multiple privacy-first AI products from the ground up,
            including encrypted backend systems and real-time sentiment analysis engines.
          </p>
          <p>
            Beyond building, I'm deeply invested in the ecosystem. As a <span class="text-text font-medium">Chainlink Advocate</span>,
            I've hosted <span class="text-text font-medium">15+ workshops</span> and educated
            <span class="text-text font-medium">2,000+ students and developers</span> on blockchain development.
            I mentor and judge at hackathons, with <span class="text-text font-medium">20+ hackathon wins</span> of my own —
            including multiple ETHGlobal prizes. I don't just teach theory; I bring what I've shipped to the stage.
          </p>
          <p>
            Currently, I specialize in <span class="text-accent">Solidity</span>, smart contract architecture, and blockchain consulting —
            along with building AI agents using <span class="text-accent">LangChain</span>, <span class="text-accent">CrewAI</span>, and <span class="text-accent">FastAPI</span>.
          </p>
          <p class="font-medium text-text">
            I build things that work in production — not just things that demo well.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Inline skills preview -->
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          {['Solidity', 'Smart Contracts', 'DeFi', 'LangChain', 'CrewAI', 'FastAPI', 'React.js', 'Web3', 'Tokenomics'].map(skill => (
            <span class="font-fira text-xs px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full tag-glow text-muted">{skill}</span>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
